From f298b00d5b18ddac1e5d494c97252f1567a7531f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 21:46:03 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Completion editing: week picker, bulk actions, per-student
 mark/reset

- Adds an attendance-week dropdown to the schedule view toolbar so past
  or future weeks can be edited without opening Reports. Syncs both ways
  with the Reports dropdown via setSelectedWeek().
- Shows an orange banner when viewing a non-current week so operators
  never mistakenly mark attendance in the wrong week.
- Student completion report gains four actions, all undoable for 10s:
    * 'Mark all N as completed' (bulk)
    * 'Reset week' (with confirm)
    * per-row 'Mark all done' (one student, one week)
    * per-row reset
- Undo uses _withAttendSnapshot so any failure leaves ATTEND untouched.
- Initial render calls populateSchedWeekPicker after Supabase loads
  attendance so the picker is seeded with real weeks.
